F(s)
f(t).
\mathcal{L^{-1}} \left[ \frac{F(s)}{s+a} \right]
\mathcal L^{-1}\left\{\dfrac{F(s)}{s+a}\right\}
=\mathcal L^{-1}\left\{\dfrac{1}{s+a}\right\}*\mathcal L^{-1}\{F(s)\}
=e^{-at}*f(t)
=\int_0^te^{-a(t-\tau)}f(\tau)~d\tau
=e^{-at}\int_0^te^{a\tau}f(\tau)~d\tau
f*g=\int_0^tf(\kappa)g(t-\kappa)d\kappa
\mathcal{L}(f*g)=F(s)G(s)
\mathcal{L^{-1}}\big(F(s)G(s)\big)=f*g
  G(s)=\frac{F(s)}{s+a} 
  \mathcal{L^{-1}}[G(s)]=g(t)  
  \mathcal{L} \left[ e^{at}g(t) \right] = G(s-a)=\frac{F(s-a)}{s}  
  \frac{1}{s} \triangleq  \int_0^t   
  e^{at}g(t)=\int_0^t e^{a \tau }f( \tau ) d \tau 
  g(t)=e^{-at} \int_0^t e^{a \tau }f( \tau ) d \tau 
  g(t)= \int_0^t e^{-a(t- \tau) }f( \tau ) d \tau 
